name: WLAnalytics
description:
WLAnalytics means of persistently capturing analytics data and provides a method call to send captured data to the IBM MobileFirst Platform server, to be forwarded to the Operational Analytics engine.

Capture is on by default.

When this WLAnalytics class's capture flag is turned on via enable method call, all messages passed through this class's log method will be persisted to file in the following JSON object format:

{
  "timestamp"    : "17-02-2013 13:54:27:123",  // "dd-MM-yyyy hh:mm:ss:S"
  "level"        : "ERROR",                    // ERROR || WARN || INFO || LOG || DEBUG
  "package"      : "your_tag",                 // typically a class name, app name, or JavaScript object name
  "msg"          : "the message",              // a helpful log message
  "metadata"     : {"hi": "world"},            // (optional) additional JSON metadata, appended via doLog API call
  "threadid"     : long                        // (optional) id of the current thread
}

name: enable
description: Enable persistent capture of analytics data. Enable, and thus capture, is the default.

name: disable
description: Disable persistent capture of analytics data.

name: log
description:
Log data you want to be captured in the context of "analytics". Some data is already captured by the framework. 
To avoid collisions, the following keys will be excluded if logged:
appStoreID
appStoreLabel
appStoreVersion
appStoreVersionDisplay
mfpAppName
mfpAppVersion
deviceBrand
deviceOSversion
deviceOS
deviceModel
deviceID
timezone
timestamp

params.name: message
params.description: The message to be logged

params.name: metadata
params.description: Any additional metadata to be added to the log message.

name: addDeviceEventListener
description: Enable analytics to capture the specified DeviceEvent

params.name: deviceEvent
params.description: A string representation of the device event to capture. Valid values are "LIFECYCLE" and "NETWORK"

name: removeDeviceEventListener
description: Disable analytics from capturing the specified DeviceEvent

params.name: deviceEvent
params.description: A string representation of the device event to capture. Valid values are "LIFECYCLE" and "NETWORK"

name: send
description: Send the accumulated log data when the persistent log buffer exists and is not empty.

name: sendWithCallback
description: Send the accumulated log data when the persistent log buffer exists and is not empty.

name: setUserContext
description:
Specify current application user. If you want user-based analytics, you must use this method call. 
For example, use it when the user logs in, and call the unsetUserContext method when the user logs out. 
Or if your application supports user profiles, call this method when the user profile changes.

params.name: user
params.description: User ID for the current app user.

name: unsetUserContext
description: Unset any user context previously set.

name: WLAuthorizationManager
description: This class manages the OAuth interaction between the device and the authorization server.

name: obtainAccessToken
description: Initiates the OAuth flow with the MobileFirst server to get an access token for the specified resource scope.

params.name: scope
params.description: Scope for which the access token is to be returned.

return.description: If success, the access token string for the resource scope. If failed, the error object with additional failure information.

name: login
description: Logs in to the specified security check.

params.name: securityCheck
params.description: The security check to log into.

params.name: credentials
params.description: Credentials for logging in to the security check in JSON format.

return.description: Empty string if success. If failed, the error object with additional failure information.

name: logout
description: Logs out of a specified security check

params.name: securityCheck
params.description: The security check to log out of

return.description: Empty string if success. If failed, the error object with additional failure information.

name: clearAccessToken
description:
Clears the provided access token.
Note: When failing to access a resource with an obtained token, call the clearAccessToken method to clear the invalid token before calling WLAuthorizationManager.obtainAccessToken to obtain a new access token.

params.name: scope
params.description: The scope whose access token must be cleared.

name: WLClient
description:
This collection of topics lists the public methods of the IBM® MobileFirst® runtime client API 
for mobile apps, desktop, and web. WL.Client is a JavaScript client library that provides access to IBM MobileFirst capabilities. You can use WL.Client to perform the following types of functions:

name: addGlobalHeader
description:
Adds a HTTP header to all requests made by the MobileFirst SDK. 
Use the WLClient.removeGlobalHeader API to stop adding the header to further requests

params.name: name
params.description: Name of the HTTP header

params.name: value
params.description: The value of the HTTP header

name: submitChallengeAnswer
description:
Send an answer back to the security check that triggered this challenge. 
The answer should be in a JSON format.

params.name: securityCheckName
params.description: The security check name that represents the challenge. Used to identify which security check requires authentication.

params.name: answer
params.description: The challenge answer to be returned to the server. For example, this could be credentials collected from the user.

name: getDeviceDisplayName
description:
Gets the display name of the device. 
The display name is retrieved from the MobileFirst Server registration data. 
You can see the device display name in the Devices section of the MobileFirst Console.

return.description: The display name of the device. For example, "Sam's iPhone"

name: setDeviceDisplayName
description:
Sets the friendly name of the device.
You can see the device display name in the Devices section of the MobileFirst console.

params.name: deviceDisplayName
params.description: The friendly name to be set for the device.

name: getServerUrl
description:
Returns the current MobileFirst Platform server URL. 
You can define the server URL in the mfpclient.properties (Android) / mfpclient.plist (iOS) or by calling the WLClient.setServerUrl API

return.description: The URL of the current MobileFirst Platform server.

params.name: serverUrl
params.description: The URL of the MobileFirst Platform server to point to.

name: setHeartbeatInterval
description:
The number of seconds between which a heartbeat request is sent to the MobileFirst server to keep the connection alive. 
The default interval is 7 minutes or 420 seconds. Heartbeats are sent only when the app is in the foreground.

params.name: heartbeatIntervalInSeconds
params.description: Heartbeat interval value in seconds

name: pinTrustedCertificatesPublicKey
description:
Pins the host X509 certificate public key to the client application. 
Secured calls to the pinned remote host will be checked for a public key match. 
Secured calls to other hosts containing other certificates will be rejected. 
Some mobile operating systems might cache the certificate validation check results. 
Your app must call the certificate pinning method before making a secured request. 
Calling this method a second time overrides any previous pinning operation.
The certificates must be in DER format. When multiple certificates are pinned, a secured call is checked for a match with any one of the certificates.

params.name: certificateFileNames
params.description: The list of paths to the certificate files. On Android this will be under the assets folder.

name: registerChallengeHandler
description: Register a challenge handler to handle act upon challenges provided for a given security check.

params.name: challengeHandlerClass
params.description: The challenge handler object implementing the methods of a SecurityCheck Challenge handler

params.name: securityCheckName
params.description: The name of the security check for which this challenge handler must respond.

name: WLLogger
description:
WLLogger is a class for logging that provides some enhanced capability such as capturing log calls, 
package filtering, and log level control at both global and individual package scope. 

It also provides a method call to send captured logs to the IBM MobileFirst Platform server. 

Log file data is sent to the IBM MobileFirst Platform server when this class's send() method is called and the accumulated log size is greater than zero. 
When the log data is successfully uploaded, the persisted local log data is deleted.

When this Logger class's capture flag is turned on via setCapture(true) method call, 
all messages passed through this class's log methods will be persisted to store in the following JSON object format:
examples:
{
  "timestamp"    : "17-02-2013 13:54:27:123",  // "dd-MM-yyyy hh:mm:ss:S"
  "level"        : "ERROR",                    // FATAL || ERROR || WARN || INFO || LOG || DEBUG || TRACE
  "package"      : "your_tag",                 // typically a class name, app name, or JavaScript object name
  "msg"          : "the message",              // a helpful log message
  "metadata"     : {"hi": "world"},            // (optional) additional JSON metadata, appended via doLog API call
  "threadid"     : long                        // (optional) id of the current thread
}

unknown.tagValue: Create or get an instance of the WLLogger class for a given tag.

name: debug
description: Logs a message at DEBUG level

params.name: message
params.description: The message to log.

name: debugWithMetadata

params.name: message
params.description: The message to log

params.name: metadata
params.description: Any additional metadata to log.

name: error

name: errorWithMetadata
description: Logs a message at ERROR level with additional metadata. The metadata is available as custom fields while creating custom charts on the MobileFirst Analytics Console.

params.description: The error message to log

params.name: metadata
params.description: Any additional metadata to log.

name: warn
description: Logs a message at WARN level

params.name: message
params.description: The warning message to log.

name: warnWithMetadata
description: Logs a message at WARN level with additional metadata. The metadata is available as custom fields while creating custom charts on the MobileFirst Analytics Console.

params.name: message
params.description: The warning message to log

params.name: metadata
params.description: Any additional metadata to log.

name: info
description: Logs a message at INFO level

params.name: message
params.description: The information message to log.

name: infoWithMetadata
description: Logs a message at INFO level with additional metadata. The metadata is available as custom fields while creating custom charts on the MobileFirst Analytics Console.

params.name: metadata
params.description: Any additional metadata to log.

name: trace

params.name: message

name: traceWithMetadata

params.name: metadata
params.description: Any additional metadata to log.

name: setCapture
description: Global setting to turn persisting of log data passed to this class's log methods on or off.

params.name: capture
params.description: True to turn on logging, false to turn it off.

name: getCapture
description: Get the current value of the capture flag, indicating that the Logger is recording log calls persistently.

return.description: true, if logging is enabled, false otherwise.

name: setFilters
description:
Filter on packages at and above designated LEVEL. 
This is a white list. Any package not listed in the filters will not be logged. 
Pass null or an empty HashMap parameter to remove filters and resume logging at the default LEVEL.

params.name: filter
params.description: set of filters and associated level (and above) to allow for logging

name: getFilters
description: Get the current list of filters.

return.description: The current list of filters in the form of  {"packageName" : "LEVEL"}

name: getLevel
description: Get the current Logger level.

return.description: A string representation of the current Logging level. Possible values are TRACE, DEBUG, LOG, INFO, WARN, ERROR, FATAL. The default value is FATAL.

name: send
description:
Send the accumulated log data when the persistent log buffer exists and is not empty. 
The data accumulates in the log buffer from the use of Logger with capture turned on.

name: setLevel
description:
Set the level and above at which log messages should be saved/printed. 
A null parameter value is ignored and has no effect.

params.name: level
params.description: A string representation of the Logger level. Valid values are TRACE, DEBUG, LOG, INFO, WARN, ERROR, FATAL. You can use the properties defined in WLLogger as well.

name: updateConfigFromServer
description:
Get and apply the configuration from the IBM MobileFirst Platform Server. 
The configuration comes from the use of the "Config Profiles" tab in the IBM MobileFirst Platform administrative console.

name: getMaxFileSize
description: Get the current setting for the max file size threshold.

return.description: The current threashold of the maximum file size.

name: setMaxFileSize
description:
Set the maximum size of the local log file. Once the maximum file size is reached, no more data will be appended. 
The file must then be sent to the server using the send() API.

params.name: sizeInBytes
params.description: The maximum size of the file in number of bytes. The minimum is 10000.

name: WLResourceRequest
description:
This class encapsulates a resource request.
The resource can be an adapter that is deployed to an instance of MobileFirst Server, or a resource on an external resource server.
The class provides several send methods with different inputs for the body of a request.
A successful response is any response with a status in the 2xx range from the server.  
A response with a 4xx or 5xx status from the server is considered a failure.

name: constructor
description: Create a new ResourceRequest object to fetch data from a resource endpoint.

params.name: url
params.description: The URL of the resource - either as an absolute URL or a relative URL.

params.name: method
params.description: The HTTP method to call the resource. Use WLResourceRequest.GET, WLResourceRequest.POST, WLResourceRequest.HEAD, WLResourceRequest.PUT, WLResourceRequest.DELETE, WLResourceRequest.OPTIONS, WLResourceRequest.TRACE

params.name: timeout
params.description: Optional. The interval in milliseconds after which the call to the resource should time out. The default timeout is 30 seconds.

params.name: scope
params.description: Optional. The scope protecting the particular resource.

name: send
description: Initiate a request to the resource without any content in the body.

return.description:
If success, a map with the response from the server. The map contain following key strings.
"responseText" - Original response text from the server.
"responseJSON" - in case the response is a JSON response, otherwise map will not have the field.
"userInfo" - user information.
"headers" - Retrieves the headers from the response.
"status" - HTTP status from the response
If failure, more information about the error.

name: sendWithJSON
description: Initiate a request to the resource with the specified JSON content in the body.

params.name: jsonObject
params.description: The body of the request in JSON format.

return.description:
If success, a map with the response from the server. The map contain following key strings.
"responseText" - Original response text from the server.
"responseJSON" - in case the response is a JSON response, otherwise map will not have the field.
"userInfo" - user information.
"headers" - Retrieves the headers from the response.
"status" - HTTP status from the response
If failure, more information about the error.

name: sendWithFormParameters
description: Initiate a request to the resource with the specified form parameters in the body.

params.name: formParams
params.description: The JSON object of form parameters in name-value pairs

return.description:
If success, a map with the response from the server. The map contain following key strings.
"responseText" - Original response text from the server.
"responseJSON" - in case the response is a JSON response, otherwise map will not have the field.
"userInfo" - user information.
"headers" - Retrieves the headers from the response.
"status" - HTTP status from the response
If failure, more information about the error.

name: sendWithRequestBody
description: Initiate a request to the resource with raw text in the body.

params.name: body
params.description: The body that is part of the request.

return.description:
If success, a map with the response from the server.The map contain following key strings.
"responseText" - Original response text from the server.
"responseJSON" - in case the response is a JSON response, otherwise map will not have the field.
"userInfo" - user information.
"headers" - Retrieves the headers from the response.
"status" - HTTP status from the response
If failure, more information about the error.

name: getMethod
description: Get the HTTP method of this resource request.

return.description: The HTTP method of the resource request.

name: addHeader
description:
Adds a header to this resource request.
This method allows response headers to have multiple values.

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the header to add to the request.

params.name: value
params.description: The value of the header to add to the request.

name: setQueryParameters
description: Set the query parameters that should be added to this request.

params.name: params
params.description: A JSON object containing name value pairs of query parameters that should be added to this request.

name: getQueryParameters
description: Get all the query parameters that are added to this request.

return.description: A JSON object with query parameters

name: getQueryString
description: Get the query string of this request.

return.description: A string containing the query parameters as a query string.

name: getAllHeaders
description: Get a list of all the headers added to this request

return.description: A list of all HTTP headers that are added to this request. Note that each header can have one or more values.

name: getHeaders
description: Get a list of values for a given header

params.name: headerName
params.description: The name of the header

return.description: An array of values for the given header name.

name: setHeaders
description:
Sets the specified headers for this resource request.
For a header that is already set, the new value overwrites the previous value.

params.name: headers
params.description: A JSON object containing a map of all headers to be set for this request.

name: removeHeaders
description: Removes headers with the specified name for this resource request.

params.name: headerName
params.description: The name of the header to remove.

name: setTimeout
description: Sets the expiration period (timeout) for this resource request.

params.name: timeoutInMilliseconds
params.description: The timeout in milliseconds

name: getUrl
description: Returns the URL for this resource request.

return.description: The absolute URL of the resource request.

name: getTimeout
description: Get the timeout for this resource request.

return.description: The timeout of this request in milliseconds.

content:
# React Native SDK for IBM Mobile Foundation 
This is the React Native SDK for IBM Mobile Foundation. 

## Getting Started 

### Pre-requisites 
1. Make sure you have all the pre-requisites for a React Native app covered. See the [React Native Getting Started](https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/getting-started.html) page if you're new to this whole stuff. 
2. Setup of MobileFirst server 


### Android 

* The first step is to create a React Native project. Let's call our app as the MyCarApp. Use the React Native CLI to create a new project. 

> `cd MyApps`

> `react-native init MyReactWallet`

* Next, add the react native plugin to your app

>` cd MyReactWallet`

>`npm install <path_to_react-native-ibm-mobilefirst_package> --save` 

* Link your project so that all native dependencies are added to your React Native project. 

>`react-native link`



#### Run your app 

> ` cd ..`

> `react-native run-android`
>

### iOS 
* The first step is to create a React Native project. Let's call our app as the MyCarApp. Use the React Native CLI to create a new project. 

> `cd MyApps`

> `react-native init MyReactWallet`

* Next, add the react native plugin to your app

>` cd MyReactWallet`

>`npm install <path_to_react-native-ibm-mobilefirst_package> --save` 

* Link your project so that all native dependencies are added to your React Native project. 

>`react-native link`

* Install MobileFirst native dependencies to your React Native project. 
>`cd ios`

>`pod install`

* Run your app. 
>`cd ..`

>`react-native run-ios`


#### Manual Steps for iOS only

1. In XCode, in the project navigator, drag and drop "mfpclient.plist" from "ios" folder.
